{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix Authentication Failure Cause Value in AS Release Message\n\n### Summary\nThe authentication abnormal case handling in the UE EMM procedures was using an incorrect cause value in the outgoing AS release message. When function `_authentication_abnormal_case_f` was invoked due to authentication failures, it would send a release request with `AS_AUTHENTICATION_FAILURE = 1`, which is not the correct value according to 3GPP specifications.\n\nThis caused the gNB to misinterpret the release cause, potentially leading to incorrect network behavior during authentication failure scenarios. The issue was observed during attach procedures with invalid authentication parameters where the UE would send an incorrect release cause value.\n\nThe fix changes the `AS_AUTHENTICATION_FAILURE` enumeration value from 1 to 2 in the AS message definitions, ensuring the correct information element value is used in the outgoing protocol message.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/COMMON/as_message.h`: Changed `AS_AUTHENTICATION_FAILURE` value from 1 to 2 in the release cause enumeration\n"
}